, to bar"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to reproach, to blame, to criticize","examples":[{"text":"أَخَذَ عَلَى الْمُؤَلِّفِ إِهْمَالَهُ المَصَادِرَ","english":"The author was reproached for his neglect of the sources."}]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to obligate"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to learn, to study"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to begin, to start, to prepare to, to set out to, to be about to, to get ready to (followed by a non-past verb)","examples":[{"text":"أَخَذْتُ أَبْكِي","english":"I began to cry"}]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of أَخَذَ (ʔaḵaḏa) (form I)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"acceptance, reception"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"seizure"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"taking away, removal"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to put under a spell, to enchant, to bewitch"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"From Proto-Semitic *ʔaḫaḏ-. Cognate with Hebrew אָחַז (aḥáz), Aramaic ܐܚܕ (ʾeḥaḏ), Sabaean 𐩱𐩭𐩹 (ʾḵḏ)."},"ipa":["/ʔa.xa.ða/","/ʔaxð/","/ʔax.xa.ða/"]}